1
00:00:04,333 --> 00:00:06,000
Here they are, and there are eight disciplinary cells

2
00:00:07,291 --> 00:00:10,500
The door entrance was here, but they later reopened…

3
00:00:11,291 --> 00:00:15,625
All the partitions together, as if it had now become a storage room

4
00:00:15,916 --> 00:00:18,916
Each cell’s area was no more than half a meter

5
00:00:19,416 --> 00:00:22,416
Sometimes a person had to sleep on one side

6
00:00:22,458 --> 00:00:26,000
Meaning that a slightly overweight person couldn’t sleep on his back

7
00:00:26,750 --> 00:00:28,583
Interviewer: Approximately how many solitary cells were there?

8
00:00:28,625 --> 00:00:34,625
The regular solitary cells were six

9
00:00:34,958 --> 00:00:37,416
As for the disciplinary ones, there were eight

10
00:00:37,833 --> 00:00:42,541
Eight disciplinary cells on one side
and five on the other, so a total of 13

11
00:00:42,583 --> 00:00:44,041
Interviewer: How long did you stay in the disciplinary cell?

12
00:00:44,041 --> 00:00:51,000
I stayed in the disciplinary cell from one week
to 10 days, meaning my time there was intermittent

13
00:00:52,166 --> 00:00:56,416
Interviewer: Tell us how you communicated
with each other in the disciplinary cells

14
00:00:56,791 --> 00:01:00,458
When we were in the disciplinary cell, they would
let us go to the bathroom during prayer times

15
00:01:00,458 --> 00:01:02,708
And the bathroom was on this side

16
00:01:03,166 --> 00:01:04,875
We would communicate with the second group cell

17
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:07,000
The one next to us

18
00:01:07,250 --> 00:01:11,916
Through the long ventilation opening. If you
called out through it, those beside you could hear

19
00:01:12,291 --> 00:01:15,791
So we used to call each other from this side

20
00:01:15,791 --> 00:01:18,708
Once, there was a young man
named Khaled al-Harbi, who was killed

21
00:01:19,250 --> 00:01:25,208
He used to talk to me. My father and I were in the cell
when the jailer heard us and sent me back to solitary here

22
00:01:25,958 --> 00:01:29,500
So through the ventilation openings we
used to communicate between solitary cells

23
00:01:29,541 --> 00:01:32,458
But in a low voice because the
investigation room was very close to us
